<HL>
   Business Brief -- Trans World Airlines Inc.:
   Airline Swung to a Profit
   Of $103.4 Million in Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
08/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   TWA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Trans World Airlines Inc. posted net income of $103.4
million for the second quarter, compared with a net loss of
$4.4 million a year earlier.
   Results included gains of $160.2 million from the sale of
Chicago airport facilities, aircraft and part of TWA's stake
in a passenger reservation system. Closely held TWA also had
an extraordinary gain of $19.8 million from the repurchase of
$213.1 million of debt.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue rose 2.5% to $1.23 billion from $1.20 billion a
year earlier.
   Operating profit before interest expense and certain other
costs fell almost by half to $43.9 million from $80.5 million
a year earlier.
   For the half, TWA had a net loss of $39.6 million on
revenue of $2.24 billion, compared with a year-earlier net
loss of $87.4 million on revenue of $2.19 billion.
</TEXT>
