   Dutch Consumer Prices Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
08/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3D
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   THE HAGUE, the Netherlands -- Dutch consumer prices rose
0.3% in the month to mid-July and were up 2.3% from a year
earlier, the Netherlands Economics Ministry reported.
   The upturn in July reflected mainly higher rent increases
that are imposed annually in that month, the provisional data
disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The consumer price index rose to 103.5 in the month to
mid-July from 103.2 in the previous month and 101.2 in
mid-July 1989.
