</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian housing starts declined 11% in July to
a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 173,000 units from a
June level of 195,000 units, Canadian Mortgage and Housing
Corp., a government agency, said.
   The corporation said the July decline provided further
evidence that weakness in house-building activity is becoming
more widespread across the country.
</LP>
