<HL>
   Business Brief -- WestAir Holding Inc.:
   Revenue Passenger Miles
   Increased 37% Last Month
</HL>
<DATE>
08/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   WAH
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   WestAir Holding Inc., Fresno, Calif., said July revenue
passenger miles increased 37% to 57.3 million from 41.8
million a year earlier. A revenue passenger mile is one
paying passenger flown one mile.
   The load factor, or percentage of seats filled, for the
month was 45.5%, compared with 48% a year earlier. WestAir
attributed the drop to last year's "kids fly free" promotion,
which boosted load factors.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company also announced that it will raise fares 5%
Wednesday to offset higher fuel prices. WestAir operates as
United Express through a marketing agreement with United Air
Lines. It operates more than 850 daily flights to 60 U.S.
cities.
   For the year through July 31, WestAir said revenue
passenger miles rose 36% to 364.6 million from 267.7 million
a year earlier.
</TEXT>
