</DOCID>
<HL>
   Business Brief -- McCaw Cellular Communications:
   Loss Narrowed in Quarter
   As Revenue Jumped 102%
</HL>
<DATE>
08/13/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   MCAWA
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
TELEPHONE SYSTEMS (TLS)
</IN>
<LP>
   McCaw Cellular Communications Inc. reported a narrowed net
loss of $60.7 million, or 34 cents a share, in the second
quarter compared with $87.5 million, or 65 cents a share, a
year earlier.
   The Kirkland, Wash., company said revenue and cash flow
were at record levels. For the quarter, revenue increased
102% to $242.2 million from $120.1 million a year earlier.
Cash flow rose to $63.4 million, compared with $11.6 million.
The company cited the strength of its operations, further
penetration into the market and the consolidation of its
financial results with LIN Broadcasting Corp., which it
acquired control of in March.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first six months, the company reported net income
of $791.1 million compared to a loss of $185.2 million a year
earlier. The latest six months includes the gain from the
sale of its Southeast cellular systems to Contel Cellular
Inc.
</TEXT>
